        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17800543" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4427252680262851949">Continuing my pilgrimage through Elllis Peters&apos; saga of murder mystery romances, I reread the Heretic&apos;s Apprentice and enjoyed it completely. It&apos;s another satisfying installment in the series. This time a young man returns from the holy land with the body of the man that he accompanied on pilgrimage. Seven years have passed since the man and boy&apos;s departure and the boy is bearing a gift/dowry for the man&apos;s ward, an ornately carved box. And the boxes contents remain a mystery for a good part of t</span>
  <span id="freeText4427252680262851949" style="display:none">Continuing my pilgrimage through Elllis Peters' saga of murder mystery romances, I reread the Heretic's Apprentice and enjoyed it completely. It's another satisfying installment in the series. This time a young man returns from the holy land with the body of the man that he accompanied on pilgrimage. Seven years have passed since the man and boy's departure and the boy is bearing a gift/dowry for the man's ward, an ornately carved box. And the boxes contents remain a mystery for a good part of the story. This one evokes the joys of living in a simpler time that is the hallmark of the Cadfael stories and is a pleasureable read. It doesn't really impact the overall character arc of the standard Cadfael crew of characters. <br /><br />Read and enjoy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4427252680262851949" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
