<div id="review_18721083" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/18721083" />
    <a title="Robyn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/778068-robyn"><img alt="Robyn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1200474005p2/778068.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/18721083?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robyn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robyn" href="/user/show/778068-robyn">Robyn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">mystery lovers, history lovers</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18721083" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14122919201407629073">It has taken me a whle to get into the Cadfael books but now that I have, I am hooked. I like the simple mystery elements of these stories and like having enough information to be able to deduce the crime for myself. I hate it when an author keeps clues to themselves so that the reader has no hope. I also like the attitudes to religion expressed through the mouths of the main characters.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

