<div id="review_378472591" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/378472591" />
    <a title="Sue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3830946-sue"><img alt="Sue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1350426069p2/3830946.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/378472591?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sue" href="/user/show/3830946-sue">Sue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=medieval">medieval</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3830946-sue?shelf=england">england</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer378472591" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11533402282910083183"> Elave enters the courtyard of the Abbey pushing a cart bearing a casket. He is granted permission to speak tnext day at Chapter and tells a tale of having been on pilgrimage with William of Lythwood (of Shrewsbury) for the last seven years. William died en route back to Shrewsbury and it was his wish to be buried at the Abbey. William had been a faithful member and contributor to the church prior to his pilgrimage and his request was granted after some discussion. The night of William&apos;s funeral</span>
  <span id="freeText11533402282910083183" style="display:none"> Elave enters the courtyard of the Abbey pushing a cart bearing a casket. He is granted permission to speak tnext day at Chapter and tells a tale of having been on pilgrimage with William of Lythwood (of Shrewsbury) for the last seven years. William died en route back to Shrewsbury and it was his wish to be buried at the Abbey. William had been a faithful member and contributor to the church prior to his pilgrimage and his request was granted after some discussion. The night of William's funeral, Elave voices some views bordering on heresy which result in charges being filed against him. When the clerk of William's household is found murdered, fingers are pointed at Elave resulting in his being detained as a prisoner at the Abbey. It takes Cadfael and Hugh Beringar working together to get to the truth.<br /> I've enjoyed the entire series so far, but this is one of the best in my opinion. I think part of that is because of the discussions on church doctrine. It's interesting to me to see doctrine that I accept without issue and how those same beliefs were considered counter to the Church of that day. It's interesting to see how they work through it so come to a decision on Elave's guilt or innocence. As with other volumes in the series, there are the characters you love, and the one you love to hate.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11533402282910083183" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


